= title('Events')
%p
  The real power of an Atlas map configuration file comes from the events element. Events are
  called when certain actions take place in the map. Anything from a block being broken to a
  player firing an arrow to the weather changing int he map is tracked and can be taken advantage of
  through an event handler.

= subtitle('Event Types')
%table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
  %thead
    %tr
      %th{:style => 'width: 15%'} Event
      %th Description
      %th{:style => 'width: 40%'} Categories
    %tr
      %td
        :xmlcode
          block-break
      %td
        A player breaks a block.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Block')
        = category('Cancellable')
        = category('Mutable Item', 'Modify drops produced from breaking the block.')
    %tr
      %td
        :xmlcode
          <block-click>
      %td
        A player right clicks a block.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Block')
    %tr
      %td
        %code block-place
      %td
        A player breaks a block.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Block')
        = category('Cancellable')
    %tr
      %td
        %code block-punch
      %td
        A player punches (left clicks) a block (and potentially holds left click).
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Block')
    %tr
      %td
        %code player-damage
      %td
        A player takes damage.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Block')
        = category('Damage Info')
        = category('Cancellable')
    %tr
      %td
        %code drop-item
      %td
        A player drops an item from their inventory.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Item')
        = category('Cancellable')
        = category('Block', 'The location of the player.')
        = category('Mutable Item', 'Modify the item being dropped.')
        = category('Removable', 'Removes the item from the map.')
    %tr
      %td
        %code fire-arrow
      %td
        A player releases an arrow from their bow.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Cancellable')
        = category('Item', 'The player\'s bow')
        = category('Block', 'The location of the player.')
        = category('Mutable Entity', 'Modify the arrow being fired.')
    %tr
      %td
        %code move
      %td
        A player moves from one block to another.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Cancellable')
        = category('From/To')
        = category('Block', 'The location the player is moving to.')
    %tr
      %td
        %code pickup-item
      %td
        A player picks up an item drop and it moves to their inventory.
      %td
        = category('Player')
        = category('Item')
        = category('Cancellable')
        = category('Repairable')
        = category('Removable', 'Removes the item from the map.')
        = category('Block', 'The location of the player.')
        = category('Mutable Item', 'Modify the item being dropped.')


